.TH READSEEK 1 "2026-06-13" "readseek 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
readseek \- hashline and structural source read tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B readseek
[\fB\-h\fR]
[\fB\-V\fR]
.P
.B readseek
\fBfile\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
.P
.B readseek
\fBread\fR
[\fB--start=\fR\fIline\fR]
[\fB--end=\fR\fIline\fR]
[\fB--offset=\fR\fIline\fR]
[\fB--limit=\fR\fIn\fR]
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
.P
.B readseek
\fBmap\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
.P
.B readseek
\fBsymbol\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
[\fIaddress\fR]
.P
.B readseek
\fBsearch\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
\fIpattern\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B readseek
reads UTF-8 source files and emits JSON for file type detection,
line-hash addressed reads, structural source maps, symbol reads, and
AST pattern searches.
.P
A
.I target
is a file path.  It may include a one-based line number or a 3-character
xxHash32 line hash suffix, in the form
.I file:line
or
.IR file:hash .
For
.BR symbol ,
it may also include a symbol address or unqualified symbol name in the form
.IR file:symbol .
.P
.B readseek
recognizes common source and project file types, including C, C++, C#,
Bash, CSS, Go, HTML, Java, JavaScript, JSON, Just, Make, Meson, PHP,
Python, Ruby, Rust, Swift, TypeScript, JSX, and TSX.  Unsupported text
files can still be detected as
.BR unknown .
.P
All command output is JSON.
.SS Commands
.TP
.B file
Detect the target file language, binary status, MIME type, and syntax name.
.TP
.B read
Print the target file range with line numbers, 3-character line hashes, and
text.
.TP
.B map
Print a structural source map with symbol kind, name, address, start and end
lines, and boundary line hashes.
.TP
.B symbol
Print the source range for a mapped symbol. The symbol can be selected by
an address argument, a target symbol suffix, or a target line/hash suffix.
.TP
.B search
Run an AST pattern against a file or every supported source file under a
directory. Unparseable files are skipped.
Output is grouped by file and includes file hash, matches, captures, boundary
line hashes, and hashlines for matched ranges.
.SS Options
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
Print version and exit.
.TP
\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR
Override detected language.  Accepted values are
.BR bash ,
.BR c ,
.BR cpp ,
.BR csharp ,
.BR css ,
.BR go ,
.BR html ,
.BR java ,
.BR javascript ,
.BR json ,
.BR jsx ,
.BR just ,
.BR make ,
.BR meson ,
.BR php ,
.BR python ,
.BR ruby ,
.BR rust ,
.BR swift ,
.BR typescript ,
.BR tsx ,
and
.BR unknown .
Common aliases include
.BR cxx ,
.BR cplusplus ,
.BR cs ,
.BR golang ,
.BR htm ,
.BR js ,
.BR makefile ,
.BR py ,
.BR rb ,
.BR rs ,
.BR sh ,
.BR shell ,
and
.BR ts .
.TP
\fB--start=\fR\fIline\fR
First one-based line to include for
.BR read .
.TP
\fB--end=\fR\fIline\fR
Last one-based line to include for
.BR read .
.TP
\fB--offset=\fR\fIline\fR
Alias for
.BR --start .
.TP
\fB--limit=\fR\fIn\fR
Maximum number of lines to include for
.BR read .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Operational error (missing file, unsupported binary file, malformed input,
cache error, or symbol lookup failure).
.TP
2
Usage error.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/readseek/cache.sqlite3
Source map cache on Linux.  The cache location follows the platform cache
directory returned by the operating system.
.SH EXAMPLES
Detect a file:
.br
.B "  readseek file src/main.rs"
.P
Read lines 10 through 20:
.br
.B "  readseek read src/main.rs --start 10 --end 20"
.P
Read a file around a target line:
.br
.B "  readseek read src/main.rs:42 --limit 12"
.P
Build a structural map:
.br
.B "  readseek map src/main.rs"
.P
Read a symbol by target suffix:
.br
.B "  readseek symbol src/main.rs:run"
.P
Read the symbol containing a line:
.br
.B "  readseek symbol src/main.rs:270"
.P
Search C++ function definitions:
.br
.B "  readseek search src 'int $NAME() { return $VALUE; }' --language cpp"
